heir lives. These range from telling the time to being a man. Adaptability, paradox, and inconsistency come to the fore in many of the essays. We find before us a human quest for opportunity and survival in a complex and changing world. This wide-ranging book contains chapters by leading scholars from the United States, United Kingdom, and Spain.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aHispanic culture.  aHispanic politics.  aSpanish writers.  abackwardness.  acultural elite.  aethnography.  agender identity.  aintellectual elite.  anarrative techniques.  anineteenth-century Spain.  apopular literature.  aracial differences.  areligious figures.  arhetorical techniques.  atemporal dilemmas.1 aAlonso, Gregorio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavies, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavies, Rhian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGinger, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGinger, Andrew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLawless, Geraldine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawless, Geraldine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMartínez del Campo, Luis G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcKinney, Collin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPartzsch, Henriette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerea, Natalia Sobrevilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSinclair, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSánchez, Raquel, econtributor.4ctb4https